      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "In commit \"tests: Reduce calls to InitS*Cache()\" (39ca267f885fd58f9467c782a72d97dc7f797225)\r\n\r\nHere and below should s/assert/Assert/. It is bad to execute non-debug code in a c++ [`assert`](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/error/assert) statement, because depending on compiler and preprocessor settings, the assert argument may not be evaluated, and this is supposed to be an example program that can be built with external compilers and build systems. Also code is easier to read and skim if `assert` statements communicate what assumptions code is making, not what code is doing\r\n\r\nIn the future it would be to good add actual error handling here, and let code work when NDEBUG is defined in general.",
      "commit_id" : "8e407571e99b0d4aad7f225b8197f35c6b6cea45",
      "created_at" : "2022-07-08T17:54:30Z",
      "diff_hunk" : "@@ -61,8 +61,8 @@ int main(int argc, char* argv[])\n     // Necessary for CheckInputScripts (eventually called by ProcessNewBlock),\n     // which will try the script cache first and fall back to actually\n     // performing the check with the signature cache.\n-    InitSignatureCache();\n-    InitScriptExecutionCache();\n+    assert(InitSignatureCache());",
